Witnesses have continued to spill the beans at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture in Parktown, Johannesburg. African National Congress (ANC) Chairperson and Mineral Resources Minister, Gwede Mantashe, has for the first time been implicated in the Bosasa scandal which is unfolding before the commission. He has been named in the ‘Special Projects’ box along with ANC MP Vincent Smith and former South African Airways Chair, Dudu Myeni. Former Bosasa employee, Richard le Roux, is testifying before the commission.    